# RAG System Design Document
## Clinical Evidence Retrieval for Emergency Department Triage

**Status:** Proposed/validation  
**Project:** Explainable AI for ED Triage  
**Component:** Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG)  
**Date:** March 7, 2026

---

## 1. Overview

This document outlines the design and implementation plan for the RAG component of our ED triage explainability system. The RAG system retrieves similar historical cases from MIMIC-IV-Ext to provide clinical evidence supporting triage predictions.

---

## 2. System Architecture

### 2.1 High-Level Design

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    PATIENT INPUT                             │
│  (Chief Complaint + Vitals) → Triage Model → ESI Prediction │
└──────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────────┘
                       ↓
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                  RAG RETRIEVAL PIPELINE                      │
│                                                              │
│  1. Encode patient query (Bedrock Titan Embeddings)         │
│  2. Search Pinecone vector database for similar cases       │
│  3. Retrieve top-k most similar historical cases            │
│  4. Return cases with metadata (ESI, outcome, diagnosis)    │
└──────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────────┘
                       ↓
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                 CLINICAL REASONING (LLM)                     │
│  Input: Patient + Prediction + SHAP + Retrieved Cases       │
│  Output: Evidence-grounded clinical explanation             │
│         (Bedrock Claude 3.5 Sonnet)                          │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### 2.2 Component Breakdown

| Component | Technology | Purpose |
|-----------|------------|---------|
| **Embedding Model** | Amazon Bedrock Titan Embeddings | Convert text to dense vectors (1536-dim) |
| **Vector Database** | Pinecone (Free tier) | Store and search 30K case embeddings |
| **Historical Cases** | MIMIC-IV-Ext (~30K ED visits) | Source data for retrieval |
| **Retrieval Function** | Python + Pinecone SDK | Query interface |
| **LLM Integration** | Amazon Bedrock Claude 3.5 Sonnet | Generate clinical reasoning from evidence |

